The depths at which samples are collected have varied over time among reservoirs, but the most consistent sampling depths have been the following:
FCR Site 50: 0.1, 1.6, 3.8, 5, 6.2, 8, 9 meters;
BVR Site 50: 0.1, 3, 6, 9, 11 meters;
CCR Site 50: 0.1, 1.5, 6, 9, 20 meters;
Stream sites (any site >= 100) are only collected at 0.1 meters (surface)
